results.name: Let G[1](q) denote the g.f. for A003114 and G[2](q) the g.f. for A003106 (the two Rogers-Ramanujan identities). For i>=3, let G[i](q) = (G[i-1](q)-G[i-2](q))/q^(i-2). Sequence gives coefficients of G[7](q).
comment: It is conjectured that G[i](q) = 1 + O(q^i) for all i.
link: Vaclav Kotesovec, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..1000
Shashank Kanade, Some results on the representation theory of vertex operator algebras and integer partition identities, PhD Handout, Math. Dept., Rutgers University, April 2015.
Shashank Kanade, Some results on the representation theory of vertex operator algebras and integer partition identities, PhD Dissertation, Math. Dept., Rutgers University, April 2015.
formula: a(n) ~ exp(2*Pi*sqrt(n/15)) / (2 * 3^(1/4) * sqrt(5) * phi^(11/2) * n^(3/4)), where phi = A001622 = (1+sqrt(5))/2 is the golden ratio. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Dec 24 2016
